The algorithmic core of this software (FFT cross-correlation alignment with
parabolic subpixel refinement, Gaussian apodization, and multi-pass iteration)
is a re-implementation of IDL routines CH_ALIGNOFFSET.pro and CH_SHIFT_SUB.pro
originally written by Prof. Jongchul Chae (Seoul National University) around
1999, with subsequent revisions through 2006. The original IDL routines have
been used in the solar physics community for over two decades as part of the
FISS data pipeline and various ground-based / space-based observation
pipelines. This Python port is independent re-implementation; methodological
credit goes to the original author.
